Description:

Similar to the ls tool in UNIX, the grid ls tool allows the user to list entries in both local and RNS directories.

The following options are available:

-l | --long

Long format

-a | --all

Shows all types of entries

-e | --epr

Shows the EPR's of all RNS entries

-d

The current directory

<target> *

A regular expression for the entries you want returned. To indicate a local path, make sure to begin the pathname with 'local:'.

Code:

Implementing Class 
    edu.virginia.vcgr.genii.client.cmd.tools.LsTool 
